CatDescriptText: Mrs. Robert B. McKee, housewife, Pittsburgh, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 24, 1959, pg. A1, with question: "Do you think that President Eisenhower should invoke the Taft-Hartley Act in steel strike?" Answer reads: "Yes, I do. It is a law designed to be used in an emergency..."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mrs. Robert B. McKee wearing hat with netting and holding package wrapped in striped paper, standing on sidewalk with Edward "Ed" Barbour in background, Fifth Avenue, Downtown
